president, wearing
the hat, and Riek Machar, his
former deputy.

03:20.067 --> 03:25.205 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Listen to this former minister
on how South
Sudan's leaders outsource
starvation as an

03:25.238 --> 03:26.873 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
issue for us, rather than them.

03:26.907 --> 03:29.910 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GRANT SHAPPS, Former Minister of
State: I
met one of the finance ministers
for South

03:29.943 --> 03:34.381 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Sudan at the U.N. in New York,
and I said,
look, if this war continues, you
are going

03:34.414 --> 03:38.285 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to find your people are
starving, because
you're diverting all these
resources.

03:38.318 --> 03:40.253 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He said, you will feed the
people.

03:40.287 --> 03:42.589 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I said, what do you mean, we
will feed the
people?

03:42.622 --> 03:46.893 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He said, I don't believe that
countries like
Britain will walk away whilst
hundreds of

03:46.927 --> 03:49.830 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
