them to bring
it down to the safe levels at 68
percent,

08:06.686 --> 08:08.588 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
or whatever the capacity is of
the reservoir.

08:08.621 --> 08:10.490 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And right now, it's up at 100.

08:10.523 --> 08:15.261 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, is there going to be a huge
volume of
water that floods through this
creek and basically

08:15.295 --> 08:19.399 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
keeps this the status quo in San
Jose and
parts of other neighborhoods
here?

08:19.432 --> 08:22.669 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SAM LICCARDO: Well, much depends
on the rains
that are to come.

08:22.702 --> 08:25.205 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're expecting another storm
this weekend.

08:25.238 --> 08:32.479 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
