contributions and donations
we're seeing pouring in now.

09:43.349 --> 09:46.586 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's a real testament to how
this community
is pulling together in tough
times.

09:46.619 --> 09:49.656 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Is there
anything else that
the city of San Jose needs?

09:49.689 --> 09:55.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SAM LICCARDO: Well, certainly,
we appreciate
any contributions through our
local community

09:55.595 --> 09:58.498 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
foundation to help these
families get back
on their feet.

09:58.531 --> 10:05.138 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But, more than anything, beyond
a big bottle
of Drano, we could use some sun.

10:05.171 --> 10:06.573 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
And we have got some sun today.

10:06.606 --> 10:10.343 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And we hope that the good
weather will persist
as long as possible.

10:10.376 --> 10:13.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's an odd thing to ask for in
California,
because we get 300 days of sun a
year.

10:13.379 --> 10:16.382 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we have just endured years
of drought.

10:16.416 --> 10:17.650 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
But we need more sun.

10:17.684 --> 10:18.885 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Yes.

10:18.918 --> 10:21.721 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All right, Mayor Sam Liccardo of
San Jose,
thanks so much.

10:21.754 --> 10:28.895 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SAM LICCARDO: Thank you.

10:28.928 --> 10:35.802 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Now that we're
one month into
the Trump administration, we
wanted to get

10:35.835 --> 10:41.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a sense of how different parts
of the country
are assessing the president's
time in office.

10:41.174 --> 10:45.512 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
To do that, we have asked
newspaper editors
from three states to tell us
what they're

10:45.545 --> 10:48.114 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
hearing from readers in their
communities.

10:48.147 --> 10:49.682 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And they join us now.

10:49.716 --> 10:53.987 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lee Ann Colacioppo is the editor
of The Denver
Post.

10:54.020 --> 11:00.093 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
David Haynes is the editorial
page editor
for The Milwaukee
Journal-Sentinel in Wisconsin.

11:00.126 --> 11:05.932 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And David Bradley is the editor
of The St.
Joseph News-Press in Missouri.

11:05.965 --> 11:08.434 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we welcome all of you to the
"NewsHour."

11:08.468 --> 11:10.603 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
David Bradley, I'm going to
start with you.

11:10.637 --> 11:13.306 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Missouri is a state that went
heavily for
Donald Trump.

11:13.339 --> 11:15.842 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He won by something like 20
points.

11:15.875 --> 11:19.779 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What are you hearing right now
from your readers
about how he's doing?

11:19.812 --> 11:25.585 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BRADLEY, Editor, St.
Joseph News-Press:
I think people are fairly well
satisfied with

11:25.618 --> 11:27.053 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
what Donald Trump is doing now.

11:27.086 --> 11:30.557 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I think he's done a lot of
things that he
said he would do.

11:30.590 --> 11:35.128 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's made a few misstatements
over the last
few weeks, but what he's done, I
think, has

11:35.161 --> 11:36.930 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
been pretty impressive.

11:36.963 --> 11:41.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lee Ann
Colacioppo, what about
your readers in Denver around
Colorado?

11:41.301 --> 11:47.140 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE ANN COLACIOPPO, Editor, The
Denver Post:
We're getting a lot of really
mixed results,

11:47.173 --> 11:48.975 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
mixed phone calls.

11:49.008 --> 11:54.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have got people calling up
really upset,
angry with the Trump
administration, angry

11:54.847 --> 12:01.454 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
with us when we have
editorialized in the
vein of he's lying.

12:01.487 --> 12:06.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then we have got a lot of
people who are
-- so we're really hearing from
both sides.

12:06.492 --> 12:09.662 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: OK, we are going
to pursue
that.

12:09.696 --> 12:11.431 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
David Haynes, what about in
Milwaukee?

12:11.464 --> 12:13.399 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What are you picking up from
your readers?

12:13.433 --> 12:15.702 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID HAYNES, Editorial Page
Editor, The Milwaukee
Journal-Sentinel: Well, Judy, it
always depends

12:15.735 --> 12:17.937 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
on who you talk to.

12:17.971 --> 12:22.909 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Liberals in our state don't have
much use
of Donald Trump.

12:22.942 --> 12:27.380 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Independents are a little bit
divided, although
they are concerned about what
has been reported

12:27.413 --> 12:30.183 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
as some of the chaos in the
White House.

12:30.216 --> 12:33.853 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Conservatives in Wisconsin
didn't support
Donald Trump in the primary.

12:33.886 --> 12:38.891 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They went for Ted Cruz, and so
they're still
a little wary and worried that
the agenda

12:38.925 --> 12:45.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of Paul Ryan, who is from our
state, may not
get passed in the way they'd
like.

12:45.131 --> 12:50.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what I hear from Trump
supporters, mostly,
is you in the media need to let
him get his

12:50.770 --> 12:52.639 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
administration organized.

12:52.672 --> 12:56.609 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I often hear them saying
that, you know,
Bill Clinton didn't exactly have
an easy transition

12:56.643 --> 13:01.147 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
either, but, in the same breath,
they often
will say, but, gosh, I wish he
would stop

13:01.180 --> 13:02.849 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
tweeting at 3:00 in the morning.

13:02.882 --> 13:07.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, what about
that, David
Bradley, in Saint Joseph,
Missouri?

13:07.920 --> 13:13.393 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
You mentioned a few
misstatements, but is
that just a small part of what
you're hearing?

13:13.426 --> 13:18.731 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What are people saying about the
tweets and
the other -- some of the
controversial statements

13:18.765 --> 13:20.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
he's made?

13:20.667 --> 13:26.906 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BRADLEY: I think people
really are getting
turned off by all the protests
and all the

13:26.939 --> 13:28.708 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
antagonism going on.

13:28.741 --> 13:34.213 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think they would just like
people to
sit back, relax, let him try to
run the country

13:34.247 --> 13:38.251 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and work with Congress and try
to get some
things done that he said.

13:38.284 --> 13:41.554 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You know, he's done 24 executive
orders.

13:41.587 --> 13:47.293 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's done -- he's appointed a
Supreme Court
justice for the Congress to
approve.

13:47.326 --> 13:51.764 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He has met with several foreign
leaders, four
foreign leaders.

13:51.798 --> 13:56.536 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He has talked with a lot of
business leaders
and labor leaders in this
country, and he's

13:56.569 --> 14:00.673 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
gotten the pipelines opened up
so they can
finish the pipelines.

14:00.707 --> 14:05.244 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's done quite a few things,
appointed 15
members of the Cabinets.

14:05.278 --> 14:08.581 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I know it's been delayed, but
he's trying
to get those through.

14:08.614 --> 14:11.951 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So he's done a lot of things, I
think, that
are going in the right
direction.

14:11.984 --> 14:20.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He's made a mistake, I think, on
his order
on the immigration from those
seven countries.

14:20.159 --> 14:22.128 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He's correcting that now.

14:22.161 --> 14:25.364 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And I think he's doing
everything he can to
try to keep the country safe.

14:25.398 --> 14:30.503 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lee Ann
Colacioppo in Denver,
again, are you hearing some of
those same

14:30.536 --> 14:32.338 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
sentiments where you are?

14:32.371 --> 14:37.376 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE ANN COLACIOPPO: I would say
that we are
probably hearing more people who
are concerned

14:37.410 --> 14:40.313 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
about the direction of the
administration.

14:40.346 --> 14:43.382 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
We are getting a lot of
protests, it seems
like almost every day.

14:43.416 --> 14:49.422 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And we should say
that Colorado
is a state that Hillary Clinton
won by about

14:49.455 --> 14:50.690 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
five points.

14:50.723 --> 14:54.794 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, let me come back to you,
David Haynes,
in Wisconsin.

14:54.827 --> 15:00.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You were saying there's a
mixture of reactions
to the president there.

15:00.800 --> 15:06.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What about on the immigration
order, the tightening
announced this week and then the
seven-country

15:06.072 --> 15:07.774 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
travel ban?

15:07.807 --> 15:12.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID HAYNES: Well, immigration,
as in many
states, is an issue that cuts
both ways.

15:12.378 --> 15:16.949 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a large population of
recent immigrants
in the Milwaukee area, mostly
from Mexico.

15:16.983 --> 15:20.720 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There was a big Day Without
Latinos rally
here.

15:20.753 --> 15:26.092 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But when you get out into the
state, out into
the rural areas, where Donald
Trump won by

15:26.125 --> 15:30.897 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
large margins, he won our state
by about 10,000
votes, small margin overall, but
he piled

15:30.930 --> 15:32.598 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
up votes in the rural areas.

15:32.632 --> 15:37.370 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In those areas, that's also
where dairy farming
is in Wisconsin.

15:37.403 --> 15:42.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And dairy farms in Wisconsin
employ -- about
40 percent of their hired hands
are immigrants,

15:42.175 --> 15:43.976 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
many of them undocumented.

15:44.010 --> 15:48.548 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so you have a situation in
that area of
the state where you have
neighbors who -- maybe

15:48.581 --> 15:52.618 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a farmer who has undocumented
immigrants working
for him, and down the road a
neighbor who

15:52.652 --> 15:56.289 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
went a Trump rally and was
chanting don't
build the wall, so it's quite a
dichotomy

15:56.322 --> 15:58.191 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
here on that issue.

15:58.224 --> 16:04.463 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: David Bradley, in
Missouri,
where you are, again, as we
said, Saint Joseph's,

16:04.497 --> 16:10.670 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
how much of an issue is
immigration and the
president's attempt to tighten
enforcement

16:10.703 --> 16:13.539 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of the immigration laws
resonating there?

16:13.573 --> 16:18.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BRADLEY: I don't think
people are against
immigration in our part of the
world.

16:18.945 --> 16:23.349 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think they would like to see
it done legally,
and they would like to go
through the regular

16:23.382 --> 16:25.251 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
legal channels.

16:25.284 --> 16:33.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have a lot of immigrants
working in our
beef-packing or pork-packing
houses in Missouri,

16:33.659 --> 16:35.094 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and a lot of them are great
workers.

16:35.127 --> 16:38.564 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we would like to see them go
through legal
channels.

16:38.598 --> 16:44.136 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And, really, the main concern of
people in
our area, they want more and
better jobs.

16:44.170 --> 16:49.375 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They want a more pro-business
environment
and not have so many
regulations, so we can

16:49.408 --> 16:52.778 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
grow the number of jobs and good
jobs in our
community.

16:52.812 --> 16:58.451 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Lee Ann
Colacioppo in Denver,
how much are you hearing from
people about

16:58.484 --> 17:02.355 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that, about, you know, kind of
like what David
Bradley said a minute ago, that
some people

17:02.388 --> 17:07.727 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just want the president to get
on with it
and start to do something about
creating jobs?

17:07.760 --> 17:12.798 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE ANN COLACIOPPO: You know, I
don't -- it
seems like, from the job
creation standpoint,

17:12.832 --> 17:16.736 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that is not one of the subjects
that we are
hearing a whole lot about.

17:16.769 --> 17:21.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think we're hearing more about
concerns
about the health -- health
insurance has been

17:21.974 --> 17:24.911 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
big in the discussion.

17:24.944 --> 17:26.245 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Immigration has been big.

17:26.279 --> 17:31.550 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I haven't heard as much from
people discussing
the economy.

17:31.584 --> 17:37.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have heard -- the bigger part
has been wishing
that so much of the kind of
national talk

17:37.590 --> 17:43.629 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
hasn't -- wasn't drifting into,
say, state
legislature and city councils
and other parts

17:43.663 --> 17:44.730 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the political spectrum.

17:44.764 --> 17:46.165 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: What do you mean?

17:46.198 --> 17:50.202 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You mean that they think more
should be done
in Washington or less?

17:50.236 --> 17:56.008 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE ANN COLACIOPPO: More that
the nastiness
of the national debate has
worked its way

17:56.042 --> 18:00.980 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
into legislative bodies here
that are usually
more civil.

18:01.013 --> 18:03.849 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Well, David
Haynes -- I'm sorry.

18:03.883 --> 18:05.718 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I didn't mean to interrupt you.

18:05.751 --> 18:11.023 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, David Haynes in Milwaukee,
is there a
sense there that the national
debate has gotten

18:11.057 --> 18:14.460 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
rougher in the last couple of
months?

18:14.493 --> 18:18.631 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID HAYNES: Well, it's been
going on in
Wisconsin for six years.

18:18.664 --> 18:23.769 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We have had -- we're one of the
most polarized
states in the country.

18:23.803 --> 18:28.941 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But I don't think there is any
question that
the national debate is more
fractured and

18:28.975 --> 18:30.776 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tougher.

18:30.810 --> 18:36.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Our newspaper, in fact, just
hosted last night
a community conversation, first
of several

18:36.282 --> 18:39.719 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
we're going to do, in which
we're trying to
bring people together face to
face across

18:39.752 --> 18:42.922 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
that divide and talk about it.

18:42.955 --> 18:47.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But it's a tough -- it's a tough
thing to
do, because we have kind of
retreated to our

18:47.660 --> 18:49.395 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
echo chambers.

18:49.428 --> 18:54.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there is a great deal of
tribalism in
terms of people are kind of
locked in and

18:54.867 --> 18:56.769 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
-- into positions.

18:56.802 --> 19:00.840 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: David Bradley,
back to you
in Missouri.

19:00.873 --> 19:04.744 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
What would you say -- finally, I
want to ask
all three of you, what are
people that you're

19:04.777 --> 19:08.848 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
hearing from most wanting to see
from this
president?

19:08.881 --> 19:15.521 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BRADLEY: I think people in
our area
would like to see a better form
of taxation

19:15.554 --> 19:20.793 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
that's pro-growth, that helps us
grow our
companies and grow our jobs in
our area.

19:20.826 --> 19:26.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think people will like to see
less regulations,
hopefully, that bog down
businesses from growing

19:26.132 --> 19:29.001 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and adding more jobs and good
jobs.

19:29.035 --> 19:36.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think they would like to
see a better
sense of communication between
all sides,

19:36.075 --> 19:41.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so they can talk to each other
in a civil
manner and get together and work
together,

19:41.914 --> 19:48.320 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
not just antagonize each other
and just wind
up trying to delay everything.

19:48.354 --> 19:53.459 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And there is an attitude that
anything he
does is not right today, and
that kind of

19:53.492 --> 19:57.630 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
attitude is not going to work if
you're trying
to work with a president and a
legislature

19:57.663 --> 19:59.398 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to work together.

19:59.432 --> 20:01.367 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Are they putting
the blame
-- just quickly, David Bradley,
so are they

20:01.400 --> 20:05.337 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
putting the blame on Republicans
or Democrats
or everybody?

20:05.371 --> 20:10.209 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
DAVID BRADLEY: I think both
sides are pointing
at each other.

20:10.242 --> 20:16.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think they wound up -- I
think there
is a way to get together and
talk and hopefully

20:16.615 --> 20:18.784 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
try to work things out.

20:18.818 --> 20:24.457 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I don't think Trump is
willing -- is determined
to get everything he wants, and
I don't think

20:24.490 --> 20:26.826 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
the Congress is going to get
everything they
want.

20:26.859 --> 20:31.097 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there has got to be some
form of compromise
there, and we can make some
headway and get

20:31.130 --> 20:33.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
this country off its stagnation.

20:33.332 --> 20:35.768 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Very quickly to
the other two
of you.

20:35.801 --> 20:42.475 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lee Ann Colacioppo, hopes for
this administration
from your people in your area?

20:42.508 --> 20:47.346 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
LEE ANN COLACIOPPO: I hear a lot
of -- very
similar to what he was just
saying, I hear

20:47.379 --> 20:54.019 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a lot of people just wishing
that the nasty
tone would come down and that
there wouldn't

20:54.053 --> 20:58.657 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
just be a stalemate in Congress,
and that
they would all be able to work
together to

20:58.691 --> 21:03.896 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
get something done that would
incorporate
the thoughts of both parties,
compromise,

21:03.929 --> 21:05.397 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
basically.

21:05.431 --> 21:08.834 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: David Haynes,
finally, in Milwaukee,
what are the hopes?

21:08.868 --> 21:13.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID HAYNES: Well, I think one
of the hopes
right now is that the White
House can become

21:13.572 --> 21:16.308 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
less chaotic and more
professional.

21:16.342 --> 21:19.445 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It really seems to be like
amateur hour right
now.

21:19.478 --> 21:25.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And for both conservatives and
independents
in our state, there is concern
that it's hard

21:25.417 --> 21:28.587 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to get anything done if there
isn't good leadership
coming from the White House.

21:28.621 --> 21:31.690 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: We want to thank
all three
of you for joining us.

21:31.724 --> 21:38.497 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lee Ann Colacioppo, The Denver
Post, David
Bradley, The St. Joseph
News-Press in Missouri,

21:38.531 --> 21:42.668 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and David Haynes, The Milwaukee
Journal-Sentinel
in Wisconsin, we appreciate it.

21:42.701 --> 21:44.737 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
LEE ANN COLACIOPPO: Thank you.

21:44.770 --> 21:48.908 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
DAVID HAYNES: Thank you.

21:48.941 --> 21:53.078 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
DAVID BRADLEY: Thank you.

